<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09154a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09154a">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09154a"> 154(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> strife stirrer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">That palm toddy of theirs has also cracked many a Luban&apos;s skull in a double sense; beginning as a harmless lemonade, it ultimately gets as bad as brandy&mdash;the <mark>&ldquo;strife-stirrer</mark>,&rdquo; they call it. This name is very pat because eloquent of the wild rows resulting from a palm-toddy carouse, each one of the black drunks beginning right off to rake up the mud-heaps of memory for a <i>casus belli</i>. <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 141</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03160e" href="c03all.htm#c03160e">VI.C.03:160(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
